<p><b>Amethyst</b> is a violet variety of <a href="/wiki/Quartz" title="Quartz">quartz</a> often used in <a href="/wiki/Jewelry" title="Jewelry" class="mw-redirect">jewelry</a>. The name comes from the <a href="/wiki/Ancient_Greek" title="Ancient Greek">Ancient Greek</a> <i>a-</i> ("not") and <i>methustos</i> ("intoxicated"), a reference to the belief that the stone protected its owner from <a href="/wiki/Drunkenness" title="Drunkenness">drunkenness</a>; the <a href="/wiki/Ancient_Greece" title="Ancient Greece">ancient Greeks</a> and <a href="/wiki/Ancient_Rome" title="Ancient Rome">Romans</a> wore amethyst and made drinking vessels of it in the belief that it would prevent <a href="/wiki/Intoxication" title="Intoxication">intoxication</a>.</p>
